SIMPLE: bracing
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bracing
<hw>Bra"cing</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Imparting strength
or tone; strengthening; invigorating; <as>as, a <ex>bracing</ex> north
wind</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bracing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Bracing
<hw>Bra"cing</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of strengthening, supporting, or propping, with a brace or braces; the
state of being braced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Engin.)</fld> <def>Any system of braces; braces,
collectively; <as>as, the <ex>bracing</ex> of a truss</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 174 --></p>

<p><ent>Brack</ent>⟦br⟧
